ciscoCacheEngineMIB.name: ciscoCacheEngineMIB
ciscoCacheEngineMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134-1706 USA Tel: +1 408 526 4000 E-mail: cs-webcache@cisco.com
ciscoCacheEngineMIB.description: The MIB module for the Cisco Cache Engine from Cisco Systems, Inc.

cceFarmTable.name: cceFarmTable
cceFarmTable.description: Cache farm table. A cache farm consists of all the cache engines attached to a single router.

cceFarmEntry.name: cceFarmEntry
cceFarmEntry.description: Information on a single cache engine in the cache farm.

cceFarmEntryIndex.name: cceFarmEntryIndex
cceFarmEntryIndex.description: Arbitrary index into the cache farm table.

cceBasicIPAddress.name: cceBasicIPAddress
cceBasicIPAddress.description: IP address of the cache engine.

cceBasicNetMask.name: cceBasicNetMask
cceBasicNetMask.description: Network mask of the cache engine.

cceBasicGatewayIpAddress.name: cceBasicGatewayIpAddress
cceBasicGatewayIpAddress.description: IP address of the default gateway of the cache engine. This is the IP address of the router that allows connections to the engine from web browsers, and that allows the cache engine to be connected to the network. If '0.0.0.0', the default gateway address is not configured.

cceBasicCacheName.name: cceBasicCacheName
cceBasicCacheName.description: Human-readable name for the cache engine.

cceBasicFarmName.name: cceBasicFarmName
cceBasicFarmName.description: Administratively assigned human-readable name associated with the router that the cache engine is attached to. All cache engines attached to a single router form a cache farm.

cceDnsDomain.name: cceDnsDomain
cceDnsDomain.description: Domain Name System (DNS) domain of the cache engine.

cceDnsEntry.name: cceDnsEntry
cceDnsEntry.description: Information on a DNS server that the cache engine has been configured to use. When resolving DNS names, each DNS server is tried in table entry order until the name is resolved. The table entry order is determined by user configuration.

cceDnsEntryIndex.name: cceDnsEntryIndex
cceDnsEntryIndex.description: Arbitrary index into the DNS server table.

cceIcpClientEnabled.name: cceIcpClientEnabled
cceIcpClientEnabled.description: If true(1), the ICP Client is enabled. If false(2), the ICP Client is disabled. ICP is the Internet Cache Protocol as defined by RFC 2186 and RFC 2187.

cceIcpClientWait.name: cceIcpClientWait
cceIcpClientWait.description: The timeout period for ICP responses. If object retrieval has not commenced when the timeout occurs, a new source is selected.

cceIcpClientRetry.name: cceIcpClientRetry
cceIcpClientRetry.description: The number of retries to be attempted before it is assumed that an ICP server is down.

cceIcpClientLocalDomains.name: cceIcpClientLocalDomains
cceIcpClientLocalDomains.description: Local domains for which ICP requests shall not be made. These are the domains for which the cache engine is closer to the actual server than the other caches and would not benefit from the ICP interaction.

cceIcpClientRemServTable.name: cceIcpClientRemServTable
cceIcpClientRemServTable.description: The remote server table contains information on remote servers (cache engines) to which ICP requests should be sent.

cceIcpClientRemServEntry.name: cceIcpClientRemServEntry
cceIcpClientRemServEntry.description: Information on an ICP remote server.

cceIcpClientRemServIndex.name: cceIcpClientRemServIndex
cceIcpClientRemServIndex.description: Arbitrary index into the remote server table. The ICP requests are sent simultaneously to all the remote servers that are present.

cceIcpClientRemServIpAddress.name: cceIcpClientRemServIpAddress
cceIcpClientRemServIpAddress.description: IP address of the ICP remote server where all ICP requests shall be sent.

cceIcpClientRemServState.name: cceIcpClientRemServState
cceIcpClientRemServState.description: ICP state of the remote server. If normal(1), this remote server is operating normally. If warning(2), this remote server has stopped responding to ICP requests. If critical(3), this remote server is sending an ICP deny response.

cceIcpClientRemServType.name: cceIcpClientRemServType
cceIcpClientRemServType.description: Configured ICP server type of the cache engine. If parent(1), the cache engine is allowed to retrieve objects when an ICP miss has occurred. If sibling(2), the cache engine is not allowed to retrieve objects when an ICP miss has occurred.

cceIcpClientRemServIcpPort.name: cceIcpClientRemServIcpPort
cceIcpClientRemServIcpPort.description: Port on a remote ICP server to which ICP requests will be sent.

cceIcpClientRemServHttpPort.name: cceIcpClientRemServHttpPort
cceIcpClientRemServHttpPort.description: HTTP port to which proxy-style HTTP requests will be forwarded.

cceIcpClientRemServSelDomains.name: cceIcpClientRemServSelDomains
cceIcpClientRemServSelDomains.description: Set of domains for which ICP requests will be forwarded to this ICP remote server. List of domains is represented as a space-delimited string.

cceIcpServerEnabled.name: cceIcpServerEnabled
cceIcpServerEnabled.description: If true(1), the ICP server protocol functionality is enabled. If false(2), the ICP server protocol functionality is disabled.

cceIcpServerPort.name: cceIcpServerPort
cceIcpServerPort.description: ICP port that the server is listening on. The port to which other ICP clients can send ICP requests.

cceIcpServerRemClntTable.name: cceIcpServerRemClntTable
cceIcpServerRemClntTable.description: List of remote clients which are allowed to send ICP requests to this cache engine.

cceIcpServerRemClntEntry.name: cceIcpServerRemClntEntry
cceIcpServerRemClntEntry.description: Information on a remote ICP server.

cceIcpServerRemClntIndex.name: cceIcpServerRemClntIndex
cceIcpServerRemClntIndex.description: Arbitrary index into the remote client table.

cceIcpServerRemClntIPAddress.name: cceIcpServerRemClntIPAddress
cceIcpServerRemClntIPAddress.description: IP address of a remote client that is allowed to send ICP requests to this cache engine.

cceIcpServerRemClntFetch.name: cceIcpServerRemClntFetch
cceIcpServerRemClntFetch.description: If true(1), the remote ICP client is allowed to request the HTTP object from the cache engine. If false(2), the remote ICP client is not allowed to request the HTTP object from the cache engine.

cceProxyIncomingPort.name: cceProxyIncomingPort
cceProxyIncomingPort.description: If non-zero, the cache engine is enabled to accept incoming proxy server requests on this port number. Incoming proxy server requests originate from web browsers that are configured to use the cache engine as a proxy server. If zero, the cache engine is not enabled to act as a proxy server.

cceProxyOutgoingAddress.name: cceProxyOutgoingAddress
cceProxyOutgoingAddress.description: IP address or name of an upstream proxy server. Outgoing client HTTP requests (for misses) from the proxy server are redirected to the upstream proxy server identified by this IP address or name. 'Upstream' means a server closer to the actual source where the object resides.

cceProxyOutgoingPort.name: cceProxyOutgoingPort
cceProxyOutgoingPort.description: If non-zero, the cache engine is enabled for outgoing proxy mode and this value is the port number used to communicate with the upstream proxy server. If 0, outgoing proxy mode is disabled.

cceTimeGmtTime.name: cceTimeGmtTime
cceTimeGmtTime.description: Current GMT (Greenwich Mean Time) military format (HH:MM:SS).

cceTimeTable.name: cceTimeTable
cceTimeTable.description: The Network Time Protocol (NTP) server table.

cceTimeEntryIndex.name: cceTimeEntryIndex
cceTimeEntryIndex.description: Arbitrary index into the NTP server table. NTP requests are sent to each server in table order, until a request is satisfied.

cceTimeEntryIpAddress.name: cceTimeEntryIpAddress
cceTimeEntryIpAddress.description: IP address of the NTP server.

cceCacheFarmHealingModeWait.name: cceCacheFarmHealingModeWait
cceCacheFarmHealingModeWait.description: Maximum time the cache engine shall wait for objects to be retrieved from the other caches in the farm during cache engine initialization.

cceCacheFarmHealingModeRetry.name: cceCacheFarmHealingModeRetry
cceCacheFarmHealingModeRetry.description: Number of times the cache engine will ask its neighbor caches in the farm for misses before it determines that the caches 'knows nothing', and stops asking. Initial default value is 200.

cceCacheFarmVersion.name: cceCacheFarmVersion
cceCacheFarmVersion.description: Version description of the currently executing cache engine object code image.

cceFreshnessTextAgeMultiplier.name: cceFreshnessTextAgeMultiplier
cceFreshnessTextAgeMultiplier.description: Percentage multiplier used to calculate the expiration date of a text object if the expiration date is not explicitly specified. This percentage is multiplied by the age of the object to calculate the freshness time of the object. The expiration date is the sum of the freshness time and the date the object was last retrieved from the server or verified was up-to-date. The object will be considered stale after its expiration date and a subsequent If-Modified-Since (IMS) request will be revalidated with the server by the cache engine. If zero, the calculated expiration time will indicate that the the object expires immediately.

cceFreshnessBinaryAgeMultiplier.name: cceFreshnessBinaryAgeMultiplier
cceFreshnessBinaryAgeMultiplier.description: Percentage multiplier used to calculate the expiration date of a binary object if the expiration date is not explicitly specified. This percentage is multiplied by the age of the object to calculate the freshness time of the object. The expiration date is the sum of the freshness time and the date the object was last retrieved from the server or verified was up-to-date. The object will be considered stale after its expiration date and a subsequent If-Modified-Since (IMS) request will be revalidated with the server by the cache engine. If zero, the calculated expiration time will indicate that the the object expires immediately.

cceFreshnessTextMaximumTTL.name: cceFreshnessTextMaximumTTL
cceFreshnessTextMaximumTTL.description: Maximum Time-to-Live for any text object for which the cache engine has to calculate an expiration date. Used to impose an upper limit on the calculated expiration date. If zero, the text object will never be cached. Units are specified in cceFreshnessUnitsMaximumTTL.

cceFreshnessBinaryMaximumTTL.name: cceFreshnessBinaryMaximumTTL
cceFreshnessBinaryMaximumTTL.description: Maximum Time-to-Live for any binary object for which the cache engine has to calculate an expiration date. Used to impose an upper limit on the calculated expiration date. If zero, the binary object will never be cached. Units are specified in cceFreshnessUnitsMaximumTTL.

cceFreshnessUnitsMaximumTTL.name: cceFreshnessUnitsMaximumTTL
cceFreshnessUnitsMaximumTTL.description: Units in which Maximum TTL for text and binary objects should be interpreted.

cceFreshnessCacheCookies.name: cceFreshnessCacheCookies
cceFreshnessCacheCookies.description: If true(1), text objects associated with cookies are cached. If false(2), text objects associated with cookies are not cached. Cacheable, binary objects associated with cookies are always cached.

cceFreshnessTextMaxAge.name: cceFreshnessTextMaxAge
cceFreshnessTextMaxAge.description: Percentage of the maximum Time-To-Live of text objects used to calculate the minimum age that a text object must be before an up-to-date check is performed with the server as a result of an IMS request. If the age of a text object is less than this percentage of the maximum Time-To-Live for text objects, then an IMS request is served out of the cache. If zero, an IMS request is always sent to the server.

cceFreshnessBinaryMaxAge.name: cceFreshnessBinaryMaxAge
cceFreshnessBinaryMaxAge.description: Percentage of the maximum Time-To-Live of binary objects used to calculate the minimum age that a binary object must be before an up-to-date check is performed with the server as a result of an IMS request. If the age of a binary object is less than this percentage of the maximum Time-To-Live for binary objects, then an IMS request is served out of the cache. If zero, an IMS request is always sent to the server.

cceFreshnessForceMiss.name: cceFreshnessForceMiss
cceFreshnessForceMiss.description: If revalidate(1), then on a forced cache miss from the client browser the cache engine shall send an If-Modified-Since (IMS) HTTP request to revalidate the object. If retrieve(2), then on a forced cache miss from the client browser the cache engine shall send a Pragma:No-Cache HTTP request to retrieve a fresh copy.

cceTcpServerSendBuffer.name: cceTcpServerSendBuffer
cceTcpServerSendBuffer.description: The size of the TCP send buffer socket for the server.

cceTcpClientSendBuffer.name: cceTcpClientSendBuffer
cceTcpClientSendBuffer.description: The size of the TCP send buffer socket for the client.

cceTcpServerRecvBuffer.name: cceTcpServerRecvBuffer
cceTcpServerRecvBuffer.description: The size of the TCP receive buffer socket for the server.

cceTcpClientRecvBuffer.name: cceTcpClientRecvBuffer
cceTcpClientRecvBuffer.description: The size of the TCP receive buffer socket for the client.

cceTcpConnectionRetry.name: cceTcpConnectionRetry
cceTcpConnectionRetry.description: Number of times to retry the TCP connection.

cceUrlFilterState.name: cceUrlFilterState
cceUrlFilterState.description: If off(1), the cache engine can serve any URL. If blockBad(2), the cache engine can not serve those URLs that are present in the bad URL list which resides in a file on the cache engine. If allowGood(3), the cache engine can serve only those URLs that are present in the good URL list which resides in the file on the cache engine.

cceEventsTotal.name: cceEventsTotal
cceEventsTotal.description: Maximum number of event entries that can be viewed at this time.

cceEventsCritical.name: cceEventsCritical
cceEventsCritical.description: If true(1), include event entries with the event entry type of critical in the event table if any exist. If false(2), do not include event entries with the event entry type of critical in the event table.

cceEventsWarning.name: cceEventsWarning
cceEventsWarning.description: If true(1), include event entries with the event entry type of warning in the event table if any exist. If false(2), do not include event entries with the event entry type of warning in the event table.

cceEventsNotice.name: cceEventsNotice
cceEventsNotice.description: If true(1), include event entries with the event entry type of notice in the event table if any exist. If false(2), do not include event entries with the event entry type of notice in the event table.

cceEventsEntry.name: cceEventsEntry
cceEventsEntry.description: Each entry contains information on a single event.

cceEventsEntryIndex.name: cceEventsEntryIndex
cceEventsEntryIndex.description: Arbitrary index into the event table. Entries are in reverse chronological order. Index range is 1 to cceEventsTotal. If 0, there are no events.

cceEventsEntryType.name: cceEventsEntryType
cceEventsEntryType.description: Events message type. If notice(1), the message is an informational message. If warning(2), the message is a warning message. If critical(3),the message is critical message.

cceEventsEntryTime.name: cceEventsEntryTime
cceEventsEntryTime.description: Time when the message was logged. Format is 'WWW, DD MMM YYYY HH:MM:SS GMT'.

cceLoggingEnabled.name: cceLoggingEnabled
cceLoggingEnabled.description: If true(1), transaction logging is on. If false(2), transaction logging is off. Transactions are logged in squid log format.

cceLoggingInterval.name: cceLoggingInterval
cceLoggingInterval.description: Amount of time that must elapse before the working log will be cleared by moving the data into the archive log which overwrites the previous archive log.

cceLoggingWorkingLogPresent.name: cceLoggingWorkingLogPresent
cceLoggingWorkingLogPresent.description: If true(1), the working log is present. If false(2), the working log is not present. The working log is a file that logs information on cache engine transactions.

cceLoggingSize.name: cceLoggingSize
cceLoggingSize.description: Current size of the working log if present.

cceLoggingArchiveLogPresent.name: cceLoggingArchiveLogPresent
cceLoggingArchiveLogPresent.description: If true(1), archive log is present. If false(2), archive log is not present. The archive log is overwritten with a copy of the working log at the interval of time specified in cceLoggingInterval.

cceLoggingArchiveLogSize.name: cceLoggingArchiveLogSize
cceLoggingArchiveLogSize.description: The current archive log size if present.

cceLoggingWriteFailReason.name: cceLoggingWriteFailReason
cceLoggingWriteFailReason.description: The reason for the failure of the last translog write operation.If the last operation was successful, then this object will be displayed as NotApplicable.

cceDiagDumpDiskStats.name: cceDiagDumpDiskStats
cceDiagDumpDiskStats.description: Number of times we got system info about a file.

cceDiagDumpDiskWraps.name: cceDiagDumpDiskWraps
cceDiagDumpDiskWraps.description: Number of times a disk partition has been wrapped in the cache engine file system.

cceDiagDumpDiskOverWrites.name: cceDiagDumpDiskOverWrites
cceDiagDumpDiskOverWrites.description: Number of files greater than 48 kilo bytes in size which arrived in a HTTP response without the content length being sent explicitly.

cceDiagDumpDiskTruncReads.name: cceDiagDumpDiskTruncReads
cceDiagDumpDiskTruncReads.description: Number of files which were deemed truncated when end of file was reached prematurely on a read.

cceDiagDumpDiskInodeErrors.name: cceDiagDumpDiskInodeErrors
cceDiagDumpDiskInodeErrors.description: Number of times a file has not been found at the expected location.

cceDiagDumpDiskCrcErrors.name: cceDiagDumpDiskCrcErrors
cceDiagDumpDiskCrcErrors.description: Number of times the Cyclic Redundancy Check (CRC) of the file did not match.

cceDiagDumpDiskDirCollisions.name: cceDiagDumpDiskDirCollisions
cceDiagDumpDiskDirCollisions.description: Number of directory lookup failures because of collision.

cceDiagDumpBufferReads.name: cceDiagDumpBufferReads
cceDiagDumpBufferReads.description: Number of physical disk reads occurred.

cceDiagDumpBufferReadErrors.name: cceDiagDumpBufferReadErrors
cceDiagDumpBufferReadErrors.description: Number of times a failure to read from disk occurred.

cceDiagDumpBufferWriteErrors.name: cceDiagDumpBufferWriteErrors
cceDiagDumpBufferWriteErrors.description: Number of times a failure to write to disk occurred.

cceDiagDumpBufferHits.name: cceDiagDumpBufferHits
cceDiagDumpBufferHits.description: Number of objects retrieved from buffer.

cceDiagDumpBufferMisses.name: cceDiagDumpBufferMisses
cceDiagDumpBufferMisses.description: Number of objects retrieved from physical drive.

cceDiagDumpBufferSeekErrors.name: cceDiagDumpBufferSeekErrors
cceDiagDumpBufferSeekErrors.description: The number of times a failure occurred in positioning the disk head.

cceImsClientRequestTotal.name: cceImsClientRequestTotal
cceImsClientRequestTotal.description: The total number of requests from the client to the cache engine.

cceImsReceived.name: cceImsReceived
cceImsReceived.description: The total number of requests received from the client that were IMS requests.

cceImsClientTotalFromCache.name: cceImsClientTotalFromCache
cceImsClientTotalFromCache.description: The total number of IMS requests from the client served directly from the cache engine's cache without revalidation.

cceImsClientFreshFromCache.name: cceImsClientFreshFromCache
cceImsClientFreshFromCache.description: The number of times the client's requested IMS object was found to be fresh (304-Not Modified).

cceImsClientStaleFromCache.name: cceImsClientStaleFromCache
cceImsClientStaleFromCache.description: The number of times the client's requested IMS object was found to be stale. If stale, an updated object was returned to the client.

cceImsClientTotalCacheMiss.name: cceImsClientTotalCacheMiss
cceImsClientTotalCacheMiss.description: The total number of IMS requests which had to be forwarded to the actual server.

cceImsClientFreshCacheMiss.name: cceImsClientFreshCacheMiss
cceImsClientFreshCacheMiss.description: The number of IMS requests which had to be forwarded to the actual server but were found to be fresh.

cceImsClientStaleCacheMiss.name: cceImsClientStaleCacheMiss
cceImsClientStaleCacheMiss.description: The number of IMS requests which had to be forwarded to the actual server but were found to be stale.

cceImsClientTotalReval.name: cceImsClientTotalReval
cceImsClientTotalReval.description: The number of IMS requests from the client found in the cache, and revalidated with an IMS to the server.

cceImsClientFreshReval.name: cceImsClientFreshReval
cceImsClientFreshReval.description: The number of IMS requests from the client found in the cache, and revalidated with an IMS to the server and found fresh.

cceImsClientStaleReval.name: cceImsClientStaleReval
cceImsClientStaleReval.description: The number of IMS requests from the client found in the cache, and revalidated with an IMS to the server and found stale.

cceImsClientRequestToServer.name: cceImsClientRequestToServer
cceImsClientRequestToServer.description: The total number of requests from the cache engine to remote servers.

cceImsServerTotalIssued.name: cceImsServerTotalIssued
cceImsServerTotalIssued.description: The total number of requests sent from the cache to servers that were IMS requests.

cceImsServerTotalDueClient.name: cceImsServerTotalDueClient
cceImsServerTotalDueClient.description: The number of IMS requests sent to servers because of an IMS request from the client.

cceImsServerFreshDueClient.name: cceImsServerFreshDueClient
cceImsServerFreshDueClient.description: The number of times the cache's requested IMS object was found to be fresh (304-Not Modified).

cceImsServerStaleDueClient.name: cceImsServerStaleDueClient
cceImsServerStaleDueClient.description: The number of times the cache's requested IMS object was found to be stale. If stale, a new object was retrieved from the server.

cceImsServerTotalDueExpiration.name: cceImsServerTotalDueExpiration
cceImsServerTotalDueExpiration.description: The number of IMS requests sent to servers because the requested object was determined to be stale according to the cache engine's freshness settings.

cceImsClientFreshDueExpiration.name: cceImsClientFreshDueExpiration
cceImsClientFreshDueExpiration.description: The number of times the cache's requested IMS object was found to be fresh (304-Not Modified) even when the object's age had expired.

cceImsServerStaleDueExpiration.name: cceImsServerStaleDueExpiration
cceImsServerStaleDueExpiration.description: The number of times the cache's requested IMS object was found to be stale when the object's age had expired. If stale, a new object was retrieved from the server.

ccePerformanceReqPerSecMax.name: ccePerformanceReqPerSecMax
ccePerformanceReqPerSecMax.description: Maximum number of requests per second the cache engine has been servicing.

ccePerformanceReqPerSecLast.name: ccePerformanceReqPerSecLast
ccePerformanceReqPerSecLast.description: Number of requests per second the cache engine has been servicing in the last sampling time.

ccePerformanceBytesPerSecLast.name: ccePerformanceBytesPerSecLast
ccePerformanceBytesPerSecLast.description: Bytes per second served in the last sampling time.

ccePerformanceSecPerReqAvg.name: ccePerformanceSecPerReqAvg
ccePerformanceSecPerReqAvg.description: Average duration of each connection serviced by the cache engine.

ccePerformanceSecPerReqMin.name: ccePerformanceSecPerReqMin
ccePerformanceSecPerReqMin.description: Shortest duration of each connection serviced by the cache engine.

ccePerformanceSecPerReqMax.name: ccePerformanceSecPerReqMax
ccePerformanceSecPerReqMax.description: Longest duration of each connection serviced by the cache engine.

ccePerformanceSecPerReqLast.name: ccePerformanceSecPerReqLast
ccePerformanceSecPerReqLast.description: Average duration of each connection serviced by the cache engine in the last sampling time.

ccePerformanceHitsSecPerReqAvg.name: ccePerformanceHitsSecPerReqAvg
ccePerformanceHitsSecPerReqAvg.description: Average duration required for the cache engine to send a hit response. A hit response is a response when the object can be serviced from the cache engine.

ccePerformanceHitsSecPerReqMin.name: ccePerformanceHitsSecPerReqMin
ccePerformanceHitsSecPerReqMin.description: Shortest duration required for the cache engine to send a hit response.

ccePerformanceHitsSecPerReqMax.name: ccePerformanceHitsSecPerReqMax
ccePerformanceHitsSecPerReqMax.description: Longest duration required for the cache engine to send a hit response.

ccePerformanceHitsSecPerReqLast.name: ccePerformanceHitsSecPerReqLast
ccePerformanceHitsSecPerReqLast.description: Average duration required for the cache engine to send a hit response in the last sampling time.

ccePerformanceMissSecPerReqAvg.name: ccePerformanceMissSecPerReqAvg
ccePerformanceMissSecPerReqAvg.description: Average duration required for the cache engine to send a miss response. A miss response is a response when the object cannot be serviced from the cache engine.

ccePerformanceMissSecPerReqMin.name: ccePerformanceMissSecPerReqMin
ccePerformanceMissSecPerReqMin.description: Shortest duration required for the cache engine to send a miss response.

ccePerformanceMissSecPerReqMax.name: ccePerformanceMissSecPerReqMax
ccePerformanceMissSecPerReqMax.description: Longest duration required for the cache engine to send a miss response.

ccePerformanceMissSecPerReqLast.name: ccePerformanceMissSecPerReqLast
ccePerformanceMissSecPerReqLast.description: Average duration required for the cache engine to send a miss response in the last sampling time.

ccePerformanceObjectSizeAvg.name: ccePerformanceObjectSizeAvg
ccePerformanceObjectSizeAvg.description: Average size of the object served from the cache engine.

ccePerformanceObjectSizeMin.name: ccePerformanceObjectSizeMin
ccePerformanceObjectSizeMin.description: Minimum size of the object served from the cache engine.

ccePerformanceObjectSizeMax.name: ccePerformanceObjectSizeMax
ccePerformanceObjectSizeMax.description: Maximum size of the object served from the cache engine.

ccePerformanceObjectSizeLast.name: ccePerformanceObjectSizeLast
ccePerformanceObjectSizeLast.description: Average size of the object served from the cache engine in the last sampling time.

cceRequestsForcedReloadTotal.name: cceRequestsForcedReloadTotal
cceRequestsForcedReloadTotal.description: Total number of times a client browser has requested a fresh copy of an object regardless of its freshness.

cceRequestsForcedReloadPercent.name: cceRequestsForcedReloadPercent
cceRequestsForcedReloadPercent.description: Total number of times a client browser has requested a fresh copy of an object regardless of its freshness.

cceRequestsNearHitsTotal.name: cceRequestsNearHitsTotal
cceRequestsNearHitsTotal.description: Total number of times a cache engine does not find the requested object(s) in its cache, but is able to retrieve the object from a neighboring cache engine in the farm.

cceRequestsNearHitsPercent.name: cceRequestsNearHitsPercent
cceRequestsNearHitsPercent.description: Total number of times a cache engine does not find the requested object(s) in its cache, but is able to retrieve the object from a neighboring cache engine in the farm.

cceRequestsServerErrorTotal.name: cceRequestsServerErrorTotal
cceRequestsServerErrorTotal.description: Total number of times the cache engine has failed to fulfill a request due to a web host problem or network problem and has generated and logged an error.

cceRequestsServerErrorPercent.name: cceRequestsServerErrorPercent
cceRequestsServerErrorPercent.description: Total number of times the cache engine has failed to fulfill a request due to a web host problem or network problem and has generated and logged an error.

cceRequestsUrlBlockedTotal.name: cceRequestsUrlBlockedTotal
cceRequestsUrlBlockedTotal.description: Total number of times a client browser has attempted to access an administratively blocked URL via the cache engine.

cceRequestsUrlBlockedPercent.name: cceRequestsUrlBlockedPercent
cceRequestsUrlBlockedPercent.description: Total number of times a client browser has attempted to access an administratively blocked URL via the cache engine.

cceRequestsIcpClientHits.name: cceRequestsIcpClientHits
cceRequestsIcpClientHits.description: The number of times the cache engine was able to satisfy a client request by getting an ICP hit from some other cache.

cceRequestsIcpClientPercentage.name: cceRequestsIcpClientPercentage
cceRequestsIcpClientPercentage.description: The percentage of total number of ICP client requests that were ICP hits.

cceRequestsIcpServerHits.name: cceRequestsIcpServerHits
cceRequestsIcpServerHits.description: The number of times the cache engine was able to satisfy another cache's ICP requests by issuing ICP hits.

cceRequestsIcpServerPercentage.name: cceRequestsIcpServerPercentage
cceRequestsIcpServerPercentage.description: The percentage of total number of ICP server requests that were ICP hits.

cceSavingsRequestsTotal.name: cceSavingsRequestsTotal
cceSavingsRequestsTotal.description: Total number of end-user requests the cache engine has serviced.

cceSavingsRequestsHits.name: cceSavingsRequestsHits
cceSavingsRequestsHits.description: Total number of end-user requests the cache engine has serviced as hits.

cceSavingsRequestsMiss.name: cceSavingsRequestsMiss
cceSavingsRequestsMiss.description: The number of requests the cache engine retrieved from the internet.

cceSavingsRequestsSavings.name: cceSavingsRequestsSavings
cceSavingsRequestsSavings.description: Percentage of hits out of the total.

cceSavingsBytesServedHits.name: cceSavingsBytesServedHits
